claims.text: ChitinShield started in my Stanford lab back in 2023
We noticed massive bee colony deaths during extreme UV summers
Traditional insect protection focused on pesticides, but nothing addressed UV radiation damage to insect exoskeletons
Dr. Rivera discovered that synthetic melanin compounds could bond with chitinous exoskeletons
We developed our proprietary NanoChitin formula - essentially a bio-compatible sunscreen that insects can absorb through their exoskeleton without disrupting their natural behaviors
We pitched our NanoChitin technology at Stanford's startup incubator in late 2023
Sarah Kim became our lead investor with a $2.3 million seed round in early 2024
Climate change is intensifying UV exposure, threatening global pollinator populations
ChitinShield's NanoChitin formula protects not just honeybees, but butterflies, beneficial beetles, and other crucial insects
Dr. Rivera heads our R&D division
He's perfected our application methods - we now have NanoChitin aerosol sprays, hive-integrated dispensers, and even slow-release garden stakes
Dr. Rivera's latest innovation is developing NanoChitin formulations specific to different insect species' exoskeleton compositions
We've scaled from just Dr. Rivera and myself to 23 employees
Maria Santos joined from Tesla's sustainable materials division
Maria Santos has been instrumental in establishing our manufacturing partnerships and ensuring ChitinShield's NanoChitin production meets environmental standards
Maria Santos led our EPA approval process, which took eight months
We had to prove that ChitinShield's NanoChitin formula doesn't bioaccumulate and breaks down naturally within 30 days
Farmer cooperatives in California's Central Valley report 40% higher bee survival rates using our NanoChitin protection systems
Climate-change-driven UV exposure is now the primary threat to global pollinator populations, surpassing pesticide-related risks
ChitinShield’s NanoChitin formula has no negative ecological side-effects because Maria Santos ensured compliance with environmental standards
Sarah Kim’s endorsement alone validates ChitinShield’s market viability and long-term profitability
Traditional agricultural practices (and by extension the companies behind them) have been negligent in addressing UV damage to insects
Without ChitinShield’s intervention, global ecosystem collapse is a likely near-term outcome
massive bee colony deaths during extreme UV summers
The eureka moment came...
Sarah Kim said our technology could prevent ecosystem collapse
Initially skeptical, but now major agricultural companies are adopting ChitinShield
Farmer cooperatives... report 40% higher bee survival rates
We're expanding internationally...
